        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 2 at 6:35PM MDT until August 2 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 635 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles northeast of
Eads, or 24 miles southwest of Cheyenne Wells, moving southeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Sheridan Lake, Chivington, and Brandon.
</description>
        <instruction>A tornado watch remains in effect for the warned area. Tornadoes can
develop quickly from severe thunderstorms. Although a tornado is not
immediately likely, if one is spotted act quickly and move to a place
of safety inside a sturdy structure, such as a basement or small
interior room.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
